Consumer prices show monthly surge in Baden-Wurtemberg 
Consumer prices in the German state of Baden-Wurtemberg rose by 0.5
percent in January from the figure for December 1996, taking the
increase over 12 months to 1.7 percent, the regional statistics office
said on Friday.
The federal statistics office uses prices from Baden-Wurtemberg, Hesse,
Bavaria and North-Rhine Westfalia to compile its provisional inflation
index for west Germany.
In December prices had risen by 0.2 percent from the figure for
November and by 1.2 percent over 12 months.
The office said that during the 12 months to January the price of
heating fuel had risen by 28.2 percent and of other fuel by 5.5
percent.
